sql:
SELECT state_id, SUM(capacity_mw) AS total_capacity
FROM renewable_sources
GROUP BY state_id;

SELECT SUM(capacity_mw) AS total_capacity_mw
FROM renewable_sources
WHERE state_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- The 'last year' refers to the time period between the current date and the same date one year ago; 
- 'renewable energy capacity' refers to the capacity of energy sources such as solar or wind power, measured in megawatts (MW); 
- A 'total renewable energy capacity greater than 0' implies that the state has at least some installed renewable energy capacity.

Demand error percentage is calculated as ((actual demand - forecasted demand) / forecasted demand) * 100, which represents the difference between the actual and forecasted demand as a percentage of the forecasted demand; 
A higher demand error percentage indicates a larger discrepancy between actual and forecasted demand; 
The confidence level of a forecast represents the degree of certainty in the forecast's accuracy; 
Access counts refer to the number of times reports have been accessed by users within each state.
